What is your artistic process?
This question previously had details. They are now in a comment.
Adam Taha
Songwriter, Creative Writing on dating and relationships · Author has 5K answers and 94.4M answer views · 8y ·

I'm going to answer as I share some images of my work as it can help with what I'm saying too...


My process starts with meaning behing my expression but also a business straegy too. I look at where I am going in life which took a long time because as a creative person, I have other diverse skills.

So I think of the bigger picture in a more marketing and strategy sense, and I had to acquire knowledge and expertise skills outside out like marketing, online marketing techniques, PR. The reason is I saw many artists struggle in bridging the gap with their work, profitability and building a system of their own than relying on far too many third party online and offline platforms.

The question always on my mind is...

"Is it good for people? Is it beneficial for the people I'm aiming at? Can it inspire, help change their lives?" Which come from a deep meaningful purpose, vision and my core values too - and help in a way that is fun, creative, using art, story telling in different formats.


My motivation from the very beginning is doing my own thing, doing it for the feeling and connect it to my greater purpose - the desire to find solutions to people-related issues. People who are like me, an artist and people who want to pursue their own path, have talent, skill but don't know how.

All this took years of reflection, changes in myself which I see as art in itself. Transforming, moulding, creating myself into becoming what I need to be to succeed in the purpose and vision I want to achieve.

I have spent my time testing online which solution to focus on the most. I've built partnerships, I've met many artists, listened to them, and did more research to help for the winning strategy.

Which now leads to the art process.

Bearing in mind what I have mentioned because it all pilots me with clarity, direction, helps ideas flow so easily, effortless every minute of the day.

1. I have the story, written and now I do the artwork for it's book. At this stage it is crazy because I am collecting references, and sketching many pieces for the characters. I use pencil, sometimes just a biro pen on paper.

I am working on the cover of the back but also getting all the characters down on paper.


2. When I have got all the pieces together and now put them together reflecting the different personalities of people, and each character has their name, lifestyle, desires, fears, hopes, challenges, influences, the story, the pain, challenges and the overcoming....


3. I begin to flesh out each character for the story line. I redraw using ink. Then I work over the ink on paper, and if I like, I move to using digital means i.e. Photoshop.

Each story will have different characters and so I bring them to life. Each one going through the same process. Sketch, the ink, watercolour. I like? Move to digital, scan and get to work....


4. I keep going until I have the illustration for the book done and I use my copywriting skills, and research to add the words.

5. Each new story in the book has a "dominate" and I take this character and begin work in bring him or her to life. But also, this becomes another new product where I will send to companies who print digital work on Canvas.

I go through the same process.

I work backwards. The background first. Then work foreground and then on the character. For the next 4 days I am working on getting main characters sorted for each chapter opening of the book and some more illustrations...


The product doesn't lead anything nor does the artwork.

It is the purpose, the meaning behind and that's even before the idea. The purpose and the vision helps me with new ideas, strategy and what is going to happen. The meaning brought other people to also work with me and who believed in what I'm doing.

The purpose, the strategy will leads the website which is being designed as a marketing sales machine and not just a static website. Friendly, with a story telling way which makes sense to the audience and the characters.

So I start with the bigger picture and I see strategy, marketing, vision as art too. An expression that happens in the mind, the heart of an artist and it pilots me to plan the business and marketing side of things.

I know you wanted to know the art process but if I left the initial stage, it won't really show the bigger picture on why I am doing it in this way and won't do justice to your question.
